Yesterday’s post, on whether or not to return a difficult-to-get-into top, had an almost unanimous verdict here on IG - but the complete opposite over on TT. 
I find this interesting, that the exact same post has such a stark contrast of opinion simply between platforms. 
Across both, mostly everyone agreed that they liked the top but here people said they would not deal with the hassle - over there they said absolutely worth it. 
My inadvertent social experiment- what do you think skews the opinion? And which way do you think today’s post will fall?

I launched a five-part course in stories yesterday and was blown away by the sweet support that it received. 
Truly, thank you. 

I’m sharing this video (though not formatted for IG 😬) here as well for two reasons: 
1.  In taping the promo, I had to highlight some accomplishments and it occurred to me that we should all create a “promo reel” as a personal exercise. It’s easy to forget or diminish how far we’ve come or what we’ve accomplished in the frenzy of getting through the day-to-day. I think you should make yours today.

2. A sort of intro as I haven’t done one for awhile. 

I guess three reasons, 
3. To “put it out there”, so to speak. To share in stories is one thing, but it feels exposed to put in feed. A few people encouraged me to do so and I appreciate it. 

We often talk about the dumpster fire that is social media but, at its best, it can also be such a beautiful space for connection, inspiration and support. 

Thanks for reading this far 🤍🤍🤍

Excuse me class, here’s the 20-40-60 Rule that I just learned:
When you’re 20, you care what everyone thinks about you. 
When you’re 40, you stop caring what anyone thinks about you.
When you’re 60 you realize that no one was EVER thinking about you because they were caught up worrying about themselves!

When I received an invitation from the @jeanpaulgaultier team to attend the @madonna concert, I knew that I wanted to pay homage to the iconic looks that he’s created for her over the years. 

I totally ran out of time and it wasn’t until *yesterday* that I called @gadaboutvintage to ask if they had anything that would suit. They understood the assignment and put aside containers of vintage bustiers, corsets and, to my delight, this cone bra that just happened to fit perfectly. The Balmain jacket was an unexpected cherry on top. 

Thank you @jeanpaulgaultier for the most exhilarating evening and start to the year.
